		Gazebo Quickstart 


1. Install and configure Gazebo

 - intstall tarfile or RPM
 - set GZBIN and GZHOME ENV vars in tcsh based user account
 - edit GZHOME/gazebo.conf global configuration file

2. Add and configure tests
 
 - add new tests to GZHOME/test_exec directory
 - edit the test specific gzconfig file in each test directory
 - create a test suite in GZHOME/submit_configs directory

3. Run Tests

 - use atc_run command to submit a test suite
 - use atc_testMgr to run atc_run in continuous mode


4. Examine Results

 - use atc_results to examine test results
 - use atc_coverage to see system test coverage

